{
  "texts": [
    "Once a neuron spikes we assume a long refractory period to ensure that every neuron spikes at most once.",
    "The construction of t ðnÞ min and t ðnÞ max is recursive with t ðnÞ min = def t ðnÀ1Þ max.",
    "The model defined by Eq.",
    "(1) is rather general and contains several other models as special cases.",
    "It is identical to the integrate-and-fire model if we set B ðnÞ i = A ðnÞ i + P j W ðnÞ ij Hðt ðnÞ min À t ðnÀ1Þ j Þ; we note that in this case the parameter B ðnÞ i depends on the sequence of spikes that have arrived from the previous layer."
  ]
}